@startuml full-app-structure-overview
package "Client (Vue.js App)" {
    component "AdminDashboard" as AdminDashboard
    component "DynamicTablePage" as DynamicTable
    component "CheckboxPage" as CheckboxPage
    component "ProcessingPage" as ProcessingPage
    component "EditorPage" as EditorPage
    component "FileExplorer" as FileExplorer
    component "CreateUserPage" as CreateUser
    component "UploadTemplatePage" as UploadTemplate
    component "ViewUsersPage" as ViewUsers
    database "Vuex Store" as Vuex
}

package "Server (Node.js)" {
    component "Main Server Logic" as ServerLogic
    component "Routes/Endpoints" as Endpoints
    component "Middleware" as Middleware
    component "Authentication (JWT)" as Auth
    component "File Handling (GridFS)" as GridFS
    component "Database (MongoDB)" as Database
}

User -> AdminDashboard : Accesses the dashboard
AdminDashboard --> Vuex : Fetches and updates state
AdminDashboard --> DynamicTable : Opens Dynamic Table Page
DynamicTable --> Vuex : Loads or saves structured table data
DynamicTable --> ServerLogic : Fetches table template data

CheckboxPage --> Vuex : Loads sections data
CheckboxPage --> ServerLogic : Submits user-selected data

ProcessingPage --> ServerLogic : Starts processing request
ProcessingPage -> EditorPage : Redirects user after processing

EditorPage --> ServerLogic : Loads document for editing
EditorPage --> Auth : Verifies user identity

FileExplorer --> ServerLogic : Fetches file list
FileExplorer --> GridFS : Uploads or downloads files

CreateUserPage --> ServerLogic : Creates a new user
UploadTemplate --> ServerLogic : Uploads template file
ViewUsersPage --> ServerLogic : Fetches registered users

ServerLogic --> Database : Reads/writes user and document data
ServerLogic --> GridFS : Handles file storage/retrieval
@enduml
